parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock assembly can cause the door to lock or unlock unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries, especially when exiting or entering the vehicle.
symptoms: The door lock assembly breaks
the door locks or unlocks unexpectedly
the door does not stay open
the door closes on the driver or passengers
the door lock system fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to fly open while driving, obstructing the driver's view and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The bolts to the hood latch come off
the hood opens while driving
the hood smashes the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door hinges can cause the door to close unexpectedly, leading to injuries or accidents, especially when exiting or entering the vehicle.
symptoms: The door hinges do not hold the door open
the door closes on the driver or passengers
the door does not stay open.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to receive a replacement jack can leave the vehicle owner without a safe and reliable means of changing a tire, which can lead to accidents or strand them on the side of the road.
symptoms: The consumer has not received the replacement jack despite requesting it
the vehicle owner is unable to change a tire safely
the vehicle owner is left stranded due to a flat tire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning air conditioning system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The air conditioning system does not blow cold air
the air conditioning system is not functioning properly
the air conditioning system is making unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning radio or tape deck can cause distractions while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The radio or tape deck is not functioning properly
the radio or tape deck is not producing sound
the radio or tape deck is making unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause steam to fill the vehicle, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents. In severe cases, the heater core can explode, causing physical harm to occupants.
symptoms: Steam coming from the dashboard
reduced visibility while driving
coolant spillage
and potential burns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent 'Check Engine' light can make it difficult for the driver to diagnose and address underlying engine issues, potentially leading to more severe problems and decreased vehicle performance.
symptoms: The 'Check Engine' light turns on and off without retaining any fault code or information regarding the problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can lead to driver fatigue and decreased vehicle safety, particularly during long trips.
symptoms: The cruise control does not work at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to lose power, leading to a loss of vehicle control, especially at night when headlights are essential for safe driving.
symptoms: Engine loses power
headlights fail at night
ignition switch failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator and alternator harness can cause the vehicle to stall or die while driving, leading to a loss of vehicle control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle dies while driving
no warning prior to incident
unresolved engine check light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel cluster module can cause the loss of essential vehicle information, making it difficult for the driver to operate the vehicle safely.
symptoms: Instrument panel cluster module failure
loss of vehicle information.
